      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, this is a good start. i think my students might ask about the downsides though. some people argue that substantive due process is just a way for judges to make up laws instead of following what's actually written in the constitution. how should i explain that critique to them so they understand the other side of the legal debate?",
